The paper deals with preventing double spending in electronic payment schemes, which is a problem in computer security (cs.CR). The problem is distributed in nature, as it involves a large collection of nodes, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed). The paper also mentions peer-to-peer (P2P) systems, which is a subfield of distributed computing and could be a relevant category (cs.P2P). Finally, the problem of double spending prevention involves algorithms and protocols, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
